@startuml CDN_System_Architecture
!theme plain
title CDN Management System - System Architecture Overview

box "Frontend Layer" #lightblue
    participant "Web Browser" as Browser
    participant "React App" as React
end box

box "Backend Layer" #lightgreen  
    participant "Express Server" as Express
    participant "WebSocket Server" as WS
    participant "Authentication" as Auth
    participant "API Routes" as API
end box

box "Data Layer" #lightyellow
    participant "MySQL Database" as MySQL
    participant "File System" as FileSystem
end box

box "External Systems" #lightcoral
    participant "CDN Nodes" as CDNNodes
    participant "Monitoring Services" as Monitor
end box

== System Initialization ==
React -> Express: Initialize connection
Express -> MySQL: Connect to database
Express -> WS: Setup WebSocket server
Express -> Monitor: Start monitoring services
Monitor -> CDNNodes: Begin health checks

== User Session Flow ==
Browser -> React: User access
React -> Express: Authentication request
Express -> Auth: Validate credentials
Auth -> MySQL: Query user data
MySQL -> Auth: Return user info
Auth -> Express: User authenticated
Express -> React: Send user session
React -> Browser: Display dashboard

== Real-time Monitoring ==
Monitor -> CDNNodes: Collect metrics
CDNNodes -> Monitor: Performance data
Monitor -> MySQL: Store metrics
Monitor -> WS: Broadcast updates
WS -> React: Real-time data
React -> Browser: Update UI

== API Operations ==
Browser -> React: User action
React -> Express: API request
Express -> Auth: Verify permissions
Auth -> API: Process request
API -> MySQL: Database operations
MySQL -> API: Return data
API -> Express: Response data
Express -> React: JSON response
React -> Browser: Update interface

== Content Management ==
Browser -> React: Upload content
React -> Express: POST /api/content/upload
Express -> FileSystem: Save files
FileSystem -> Express: File paths
Express -> MySQL: Store metadata
Express -> CDNNodes: Distribute content
CDNNodes -> Express: Deployment status
Express -> React: Success response
React -> Browser: Show results

== Alert System ==
Monitor -> CDNNodes: Health check
CDNNodes -> Monitor: Status data
alt Critical issue detected
    Monitor -> MySQL: Create alert
    Monitor -> WS: Broadcast alert
    WS -> React: Real-time alert
    React -> Browser: Show notification
end

@enduml